      "side": 1,
      "message": "Line 1908: 🟡 Suggestions - `loadMissingBodyOverwrites()` treats messages with no overwrite as permanently missing because it only writes `pluginData[\"bodyOverwrite\"]` when the transform returns a non-empty value. Conversations with many untranslated/plain messages will be reprocessed on every load or plugin attach, repeatedly invoking plugin transforms for messages that were already checked. Add a local processed marker, or cache negative results separately from the displayed `bodyOverwrite`.\n\n```suggestion\nit-\u003esecond-\u003epluginData[\"bodyOverwriteChecked\"] \u003d \"true\";\nif (!boIt-\u003esecond.empty())\n    it-\u003esecond-\u003epluginData[\"bodyOverwrite\"] \u003d boIt-\u003esecond;\n```",
