      "message": "[Critical] Line 321: 🔴 Critical Issues - `transformSwarmMessages` holds `mtx_` while calling plugin code. Other methods in this patch explicitly avoid this because plugin callbacks can invoke services that acquire the same mutex, causing deadlocks; plugins can also perform slow work and block all chat-service state. Snapshot the eligible handlers under the lock, then call `handler-\u003etransformSwarmMessages(...)` after releasing it.\n\n```suggestion\nstd::vector\u003cChatHandler*\u003e handlersToCall;\n{\n    std::lock_guard const lk(mtx_);\n    // populate handlersToCall for toggled/allowed handlers\n}\nfor (auto* handler : handlersToCall)\n    handler-\u003etransformSwarmMessages(messages, accountId, conversationId);\n```",
